chat_history: Mozart: Oh. Everybody's here! We've got guests. Good. I've brought some more.
Narrator: He opens the door wide to admit Schikaneder and the girls.
Mozart: We'll have a little party. Come in. Come in. You know Herr Schikaneder? (to a girl) This is! a very nice girl.
Constanze: These gentlemen are from Salzburg.

Mozart: Salzburg. We were just talking about Salzburg. (to the two men, jubilantly) If you've come from my friend the Farts bishop, you've arrived at just the right moment. Because I've got good news for him. I'm done with Vienna. It's over, finished, done with! Done with! Done with!
Constanze: Wolfi! Your father is dead.
Narrator: The first loud chord of the Statue scene from Don Giovanni sounds. Mozart stares.
